HEADWORD: Deprivable
<hw>De*priv"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Capable of
being, or liable to be, deprived; liable to be deposed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Kings of Spain . . . <qex>deprivable</qex> for their
tyrannies.</q> <rj><qau>Prynne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deprivation</ent>⟦br⟧
